      <h1 class='title'>Equality Commission for Northern Ireland</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 September 2003 vol 410 cc4-5WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_4ws' title='Col. 4WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 September 2003 vol 410 c4WS' name='column_4ws' href='#column_4ws' rel='bookmark'>4WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0410P2_20030908_CWS_6'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-paul-murphy' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0410P2_20030908_CWS_6' title='Link to this speech by Mr Paul Murphy' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-paul-murphy" title="Mr Paul Murphy">The Secretary of State for Northern Ireland (Mr. Paul Murphy)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Under s73(2) of the <a href="/acts/northern-ireland-act-1998">Northern Ireland Act 1998</a>, I have appointed nine new Commissioners to the Equality Commission for Northern Ireland. They are:<ul>
          <li>Anne O'Reilly (Deputy Chief Commissioner) Annie Campbell</li>
          <li>Brian Carlin</li>
          <li>Eileen Evason</li>
          <li>Tom Haverty</li>
          
          <col>5WS</col>
          <li>Michael Rea</li>
          <li>Audrey Simpson</li>
          <li>Daphne Trimble</li>
          <li>Derick Wilson</li>
          </ul></p><p>The appointments took effect from 2 August 2003 and last for three years.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
